<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5>each to his own • every man for himself</xh5><p> <i>each to his own—</i>is used to say that it is acceptable for people to have different preferences: “I find it hard to believe that anyone enjoys gardening.” “Ah well, <u>each to his own</u>.”</p><p><i>every man for himself—</i>said of people trying to save themselves from a difficult situation without trying to help anyone else: “It was not the behaviour of a friend.” “My dear boy,” he said. “Have you not yet learnt that it’s <u>every man for himself</u>?”</p> </entry>
